My music touches the whole world. It reaches the ears through Spotify and touches the heart through energy waves infinitely greater than any streaming services and algorithms can calculate. 

It's multi-dimensional, and we are here to go beyond all limitations.

So these numbers are more like it. 🕶️

Shout out to everyone who has been dancing, singing, and meditating with my music.

I can remember playing live shows and making big bucks hustling those CDs! It’s no secret that streaming platforms pay artists fractions of a penny for streams. It's a bummer and a BLESSING! As it's all a natural movement toward how music is meant to be valued in the future.

Spotify was a genius innovation, allowing us to have every song we want with a click of a button. Can you feel the winds changing? A new way of connection is coming. It’s impossible to know exactly what that will look like, but my team and I are dedicated to keeping our finger on the pulse...

Here is one of our next steps to show gratitude to everyone who tunes in and listens to the music...😲

We’re dropping a new track tomorrow with the option to support me and my music by purchasing royalty shares for the way and becoming directly invested in the project. 

Are you feeling that? Would you be interested in being part owner of my next song?

Bonus - If you’re a Spotify listener and I’m in your top 5 artists. Take a screenshot & DM me or share to story for a special surprise.

Gratitude and love to all of you for being on this journey with me!

Today I dropped a new version of one of my most popular musical offerings! "Surrender (Cosmic Mix)" is designed for a deep sound healing dive into the unknown.

It's a nervous system reset, a track that was previously only available to the Surrender NFT holders, and we're dropping it today with a special twist. 

For me, music offers a potent space of Surrender. A place that allows me to alchemize what is no longer serving me into creative expression.

This is the first song in the Sri Kala catalog where we are offering you the ability to buy royalty shares and be a part of the new music industry.

#Kalarhythm Interview Session #11 with Jackson Whalan. @jacksonwhalanmusic 

11 years of friendship. Jackson talks with me about the creative process of his new song "Imagine". Tune in for some serious artist songwriter codes and lyrical mastery.

"Anuwe" is a journey into rhythm made for both dance and meditation. This song came to me years ago in a looping session where I set the intention to sing the depth of my grief and celebration.

In that session, I wanted to go beyond toning and bring in words. I desired the phonetics to come to me, for me to move my mouth to the truth of where I was in my heart. So I surrendered to this and surrendered again and again until I began to sing the word "Anuwe."
 When it arrived, my cells lit up. It felt so right! When I surrendered just a little bit more and asked if that was it, the phrase, "Anuwe nin so" came through. 
 When I revisited the song two years later, it felt like the time to refine the track and bring it to the world. That very night I woke up in the early morning, 3 am, was an inner fire to discover the meaning of the words I channeled. 
When I searched "Anuwe," it came up as "mercy" in the Nigerian language  Hausa. I then looked up "Anuwe nin so," and it came up as "I love you" in Hausa. Hausa is a language I have no connection to in 'knowing,' but it's a Nigerian language, the land where my ancestors are from. 
For me, it's hard to physically trace back my ancestry because it stops at a certain point, with my family being brought over from Africa to the islands. So to be given this gift, to reconnect with my ancestors through sound vibration, through my desire, through my calling. It blew my mind.

When I went deeper, I discovered that "Anuwe nin so" means two things. 'I love you' in Hausa and 'what a pity' in Yoruba. Yoruba is another Nigerian language embedded into my DNA, a connection point to a past I've sometimes felt was lost. 
How beautiful for these words to come through me, representing grief and celebration, darkness and light.
I'm sharing this story to impart to you that nothing is ever lost. All of your ancestors are here to bless you right now. They are speaking to you, calling to you, and working through you. The more we surrender to listening, the more they can welcome themselves through us and move into the earth.

 As you drop into this song, recognize the magnitude of this simple act of tapping into the core truth of who you are.

Friends,

Have you ever felt like knowing who you are and how to be authentic was an uphill battle? Perhaps you have felt like you don’t know where to start with integrating your whole self. Maybe you’ve experienced past adversaries and trauma that leads you feeling like you want to hide or shameful. You may even feel out of integrity and unsure how to allow your most liberated self to shine forward, to grace the world with your gifts! 

Have you ever wished you understood how to express your most True, Authentic, Motivated and integrated self with confidence? Can you imagine working through inauthenticity and feeling empowered, integrated and confident to move forward with your most liberated self sharing your gifts and true self?

If so, you will want to check out my interview with TamRa Wich’Ma and the True Me Integration, https://truemeintegration.com/srka.

Whether it's been toning, chanting, or freestyle words, my voice has supported me in answering any challenge that's been presented.

In my family lineage, it was superhuman to speak up in a world where we were told to shut up and stay in our place. To find ways to keep our spirits lifted as they tried to take our freedom away.

Now we sing because we know how it heals the atmosphere around us. We sing because we understand that it vibrates our cells and frees up our energy. We sing because when we surrender our true self is already singing.

In my one on one programs, I've been pretty versatile in what I bring to the table and now I'm focusing the energy completely on vocal freedom.

Let me tell you about this new offering...

 Vocal Freedom is a journey into authentic self-expression.  This one on one program is not just about singing, it's about tapping into your deeper self and expressing your truth.

Through this program, you'll release the tension and tightness in your voice and body, allowing for a more free-flowing expression. You'll also explore the depths of your emotions, finding healing and personal growth along the way. Plus, you'll have the opportunity to retrieve lost parts of yourself, connect with your ancestors, and optionally create a fully mixed and mastered song.

If this speaks to your soul let's chat. Check the link in bio or head over to srikala.com/vocalfreedom and my team will reach out. Or send me a text or DM if you have my contact. 

With love
Sri Kala 

 #VocalFreedom #AuthenticSelfExpression #vocalsoundhealing #vocalwork

🥳The art of PLAY🥳

I used to never jam because I was too perfectionistic and silently judged everything I did, even in low pressure situations. My inner critic got the best of me and I felt very shy when I was around jam sessions.

Now (after a lot of deconditioning), it’s all about FREEDOM and PLAY for me.

I love helping beautiful humans unlock their creativity—whether they are seasoned artists or just starting to play music! Witnessing them learn new things by playing around brings me so much joy!

In fact, some of my clients in the past year had little to no musical background and we still made AMAZING things by playing together.

Watch me and @srikalagram make a beat from scratch and just be in the moment, not judging anything but letting it flow.

What are some ways you like to play—in music or another form of art/life?

Hugs,

Laura

🎵 Big News:

One of my greatest pleasures is to help the big hearts of this world bring their music into this world. I'm excited to announce today's release of @jennidelillo  new song "Let It Be Dark". She came to LA and we dove in for 3 days straight and created a masterpiece. 

She's a brilliant force of love in this world and I'm honored to be on her team!

"Let It Be Dark" is a poetic soundscape that touches upon the process of mourning a loss – not just of loved ones but also the loss and rediscovery of self through life's chapters. 

The creation of this song was a deeply fluid experience. Born from vulnerability and raw emotions, it reminds us to honor and witness each other's pain and sorrow, offering the respect it deserves. 

Search for Let It Be Dark by Jenni DeLillo on all platforms.  ❤️🎵

collaboration with Sri Kala
Produced, mixed, and mastered by Sri Kala

In 2017 It healed my broken heart when I was at my lowest.

Today is a day of heartache. As my Granny, Eileen Roach, left sooner than I would have wanted her too. At this time in my life when I feel the most hungry to know more about my family. 

  This morning her funeral was live streamed from Barbados and although it felt right not to go, watching the video... I wanted to be there. 

I remember her humor, her fried sweet plantains (cut the long way 🧐), doing crossword puzzles looking out of the window of her Brooklyn brownstone.

I went to New York to see her in May, she was on her way out and could barely move, and she had enough energy to lean up and grab my kyanite pendant, open her eyes, look at me like "what is this thing?!?" and pass out again. Although they said she clinically couldn't understand what was happening, I knew she felt me and her family's prayers. 

She left this world on Sri Krishna Janmastami... One of the holiest days celebrated around the world.... Like she was trying to send me a message. Then her funeral was on Amritananda Mayi or Amma's birthday celebration, the Indian hugging saint that first introduced me to Krishna. No coincidences. 

My mission is to reconstruct my family tree, write a book and make a film about my family and retracing our lineage back to the mother land of Africa. Please give me your blessings on this. 

They say time is an illusion... 
Today gives me the sense that time is of the essence.

So many questions, so little time.
Please cherish these moments with your family..

Sending love to my family on this day as they say goodbye and see you soon. 

Sri

I FELT MY WAY HOME 🎵 I arrived in tears at the studio on the last day after receiving some difficult news… On top of a week of big feelings.

I “pulled myself together” before walking in so I could clear my voice, focus and get all the recording done that needed to get done. It was set to be a very full completion day.

When @jessejohnsoncoaching and @srikalagram invited me to begin the day on the harmonium, my heart opened up to feeling ALL OF IT. 

I remember saying to Sri and J @bravekindsoul - “I feel like I need to close my heart to be able to get everything done I need to get done today, but I can’t do that. I can’t sing if it’s not from the depths of my heart. And when I go there it hurts and is all consuming.”

They reminded me that all great art comes from raw feeling.

They guided me through working with all the emotion, making MORE space for it on my body, and channeling it into the music, transmuting it through sound. 

In many ways I already knew how to do this. I turn to sound to be with my emotions often, and this whole music journey began as part of my heart-healing post divorce and other journeys of gratitude and grieving over the past 3 years.

But the safe witnessing space J Brave + Sri held for me invited me to take this to a new level of depth and feeling. 

The sounds that came out felt raw, visceral, true.

As I made space at the mic for feeling and for my human self - tears, wailing, and all - my heart opened even more.

The sounds, codes and words that channeled through following this inner alchemy were 🔥 🔥 🔥 

It is a potent time for codes to drop right now. The Great Mother has important messages to share with all her children about humanity + Love + respect for life. 

What an honor to be a vessel and voice for her fierce Love. 

**********************
I speak for the Mother
Calling all her children
Unplug the machine
Let all your breath in 
*********************

Thank you also to @colinyouhome and @soul.fluency for bringing additional care and support to this day, including harmonies, altarcraft, @tribalmarkers, ceremony, and Tiramisu. 

Love, All-ways.
♥️ Catarina

Gate 50 #humandesigntransit of the day.

Tribal energy. Knowing what the tribe needs for nourishment.
Last week's gate prepared us for this by welcoming in change. 

Now it's time to harvest last week's blessings. 

The current position of the gate (line 2 hermit) says we can either be strong in the face of opposition or be in discomfort and withdraw. 

Both sides are important for the world to experience. The  pause and the strength. The world evolves and heals through playing out detriments. At the same time there are those I want to inspire to not take your art down and delete your presence in this time... Your creative hearts are the most needed right now.

You have come a long way, and some of the things you've learnt on the journey goes against those out dated societal rules. So there can be some fear of retribution if you stand strong in your values. You are not alone.

If you find yourself in withdrawal... Make art. Express your discomfort on the canvas of paint or music and that will bring you through the other side with some blessings to share. Have faith and let it breathe..

GATE 28: The Game player
LINE 2: Distasteful Alliance

Today's Human design Transit. 

I'm loving this new documentary series about #JohnGotti named #GetGotti. It paints the perfect picture of this gate in action. John Gotti had 28.2 exalted in his conscious sun. Which also means it's his birthday. 

Although human design gates or lines can sometimes sound negative you can also see them as superpowers. In this case for a supervillain. (The rest of his chart paints the full picture 31 - Influence, 7 in mars - warlike leadership)

Gotti had the superpower of Distasteful Alliance. Which allowed him to use things that others would never use to accomplish his goals. Although his crimes and murders were the most Distasteful... Having 28.2 created the aura for his community to be okay with his crimes, and most times glorify him. He was one of the first mobsters to be a known murderer and so famous that he was on the front cover of Time magazine. 

Those with the 28 really want to have fun with the game of life. They know how to take risks and that suffering leads to growth. 

John Gotti wanted to be remembered forever as a great game player more than he wanted to live a long or free life. 

He died in prison at 61, but today he's got the #1 Netflix documentary. 🤷🏿

How is the gate of the game player "playing" out for you this week?
